dct_description_sm: This polygon data layer represents an index grid for Wisconsin based on latitude and longitude intervals corresponding to the USGS topographic quadrangle series at 1:24,000 scale. The latitude/longitude interval corresponding to this quadrangle index is 7.5 minutes latitude by 7.5 minutes longitude. The dataset was originally published by the Wisconsin Department of Natural Resources on April 3, 2019. [This polygon layer provides an index grid based on latitude and longitude intervals corresponding to the USGS topographic quadrangle series at 1:24,000 scale. The latitude/longitude interval corresponding to this quadrangle index is 7.5 minutes latitude by 7.5 minutes longitude.]
